Kepa: The Kepa is not a very strong monster. However, attacking it recklessly may bring you to tears.
Humans sometimes hunt Large Kepa for food.
Most people are unaware that the Red Kepa is actually quite similar to the Kepa.
Despite its tough skin, the Hamming is a fairly feeble monster.
Originally stalks of plants, the Chinency have since evolved to their current form.
Very little is known about the Jukopus' internal structure.
Depending on its maturity this monster may develop a variety of different techniques.
Precautions should be taken before fighting this monster.
The meat of this monster is quite nutritious.
The souls of those who ventured to the underworld now show up as demons.
A soul that did not receive the guidance of the Goddess. It was born in response to the control of demons.
Crawling in the forest shadows, this monster evolved greatly in size over time.
This monster evolved from a more deadly and vicious beast.
It is unknown whether Vubbe Fighters are trained or have a natural aptitude for combat.
Some people use a Meduja child to contact the souls of the dead.
Research claims that souls reside within the Meduja plant.
Rather than engaging these monsters up-close, it is better to strike them from afar.
Former soldiers led by General Ruklys during the civil war, at the time when demons attacked. Ruklys' betrayal to them is a secret that has been obscured from history.
Puragi, like some other monsters, like to deodorize themselves with biocides.
No one has ever seen the face hidden behind the mask it wears.
A demon minion that is found throughout the world.
This fisherman's actions are often hieroglyphic.
Its stem head can be used for various purposes such as releasing attractants.
Whether the Matsum originated from a plant, animal, or mineral is unimportant. What you should know is that they are dangerous.
The brightly colored eyes make these monsters hard to miss.
Someone once described this monster as hard to block and hard to eat.
A large loathsome creature that is intentionally hunted.
Kepas have aged the Pokusaku flower through constantly leaching it. Caution is advised as it emits a strong spicy scent.
Its dilapidated color from aging through life only substantiates its danger.
The leaves of this plant are stronger than leather.
Even after undergoing mutations Raffly continue to hunt small insects.
Having evolved around water, its entire body is now made of solid wood.
Attacking its legs will not cause it to topple over.
Ghost affected by the demons tend to change their appearances like this.
Unlike other monsters in Myan Leong Ryu, these monsters often were evil souls even when they were living.
This floating seed has transmutated, losing its outer fluff for a solid shell.
It would be a real blessing if the Woodman couldn't move.
Its slimy substance allows it to model itself into a prototype of the object it last encountered, thus the slime can exist in a variety of types.
During the times of Zachariel the Great, these monsters were placed to stop intruders. Its name stems from grave robbers who encountered it.
Court sorcerers created the Madakia to fend off intruding grave robbers.
In order to watch over sealed ruins that lacked an overseer, monsters were created with a diversity of magic. The wheelen is one of these monsters.
The stone Calvary of the Royal Mausoleum are magically assembled to withstand even the heavily armed knight.
Though the reason is unknown, this monster has an extreme hatred towards humans. It loves to attack them for food and survival.
Fallen Hanaming leaves usually don't wither rapidly.
Their numbers grew after the Great Plant Cataclysm; now they tend to compete with humans for territory.
Chupacabras move secretly. Based on this, it is more dangerous for humans if there are elite Chupacabras.
Some say a Popolion's voice can even break glass bottles.
It is a mutated monster for Tontulia to be more active.
The lives of residents in the dry and harsh environment were further impacted when the cacti mutated to Tontus.
Vekarabe are more circular compared to similar creatures. However, it is no less aggressive than its peers.
The name of this monster suits its appearance, as it doesn't have any reflection.
One of the defensive systems left in the king's tomb.
Early pioneers came up with its name from its similarity to the Gepetto.
Monsters that have simply grown in size and become more aggressive are rather relieving.
This stationary monster is especially hostile towards humans, but it will still attack all warm-blooded animals.
Although originally created to defend the Royal Mausoleum, it has since malfunctioned into a state that attacks anyone who enters.
While this Cockatrice is fairly small, its terrifying breath and glance can petrify its foes instantly.
Though their appearance can be mistaken with other similar-looking monsters, Zinutekas are artificially constructed by magic.
Despite its appearance, the Pokubu can be a ferocious beast.
What's more frightening than Dandel's keratinized soft hair is its vitality and aggressiveness.
Because of its environment this monster has adapted to various forms. This one has evolved to have wings.
These creatures are not hollow on the inside.
Originally created with good intentions, the golem now lives, possessed by evil forces.
A lesser demon summoned by its superiors in the Demonic realm to invade towers.
These lesser demons come in countless types due to their populous numbers.
These species were once fairly rare; however, in recent times their numbers have greatly increased.
The Big Cockatrice is quite dangerous, as its glare and breath can petrify any opponents. Engaging this creature should not be taken lightly.
The number of Bagworms is no longer increasing, yet its current population is enough not to worry about extinction.
Its body vanishes if you stay away from it for a long time.
It used its hook on a large monster to come over from the Demon realm, and has underwent a lot of change.
Even though there are less logging activities, the monsters that originated from the stumps continue to show up. They appear to be formed out of the residues of plant type monsters.
A popular theory is that you have to be a demon to use this messenger.
Over time these Vubbes have become diverse and distinguishable.
It is hard to determine whether their mining roles are permanent since little is known about the Vubbe's social system.
Vubbe Archers specialize in using ranged weapons. Thus some people claim Vubbes have specific roles.
It is possible to collect and use the bows and arrows that the Vubbes made.
A shrub monster that attacks by either firing its twigs or striking with its branches.
According to legend this watchdog is a creation that Zachariel the Great had planned to preserve.
Due to its cute appearance many people have tried to win over Tiny's heart, but none were successful.
Tree Ambulo is different from the typical monsters that originated from the demon realm as it is not a deformity between creatures and things.
It's well-trained to follow its owner's every command. Unfortunately, its owner is usually a demon.
Shredded is a demon monster that was derived from the by-product that results when you transform a monster into a powerful ghost.
Yekub unleashes its infamous cry in the Demon realm, which produces many minions and spreads them around the world. Yekubite is the name given to these minions.
A possessed demonic statue in the image of the Goddess.
This monster does not seem to transmute from typical plants but rather from rotten flora. However, there are no evidence to support this conclusion.
Upon transforming into a monster with a hardened wood body and no leaves, Treegool supplants its former photosynthetic diet with hunting.
Existing since ancient times, Ammon has harmed countless people and monsters.
While it has maintained its original form, Operor has developed severely aggressive and violent behavior.
A severely mutated bee and beetle hybrid with qualities of both, it operates in swarms.
Before it was revealed to be a mutated plant, it was speculated to be a monster's larvae.
Animals living in the Royal Mausoleum have been deformed in recent years by the influence of the Magi.
It is a magic creature whose name comes from the wishes of a golem species.
A magical creature created to protect the Royal Mausoleum. Despite being weak, it is strong enough to resist the Goddess' powers.
Despite its appearance, this magical creation has received the blessing of the Goddess. Can deal critical damage to demons.
Many creatures have been placed in the Royal Mausoleum, including the Tombsinker, to guard against intruding demons.
There are rumors saying the Weaver is looking for thread made of stone.
Please do not look directly into their hoods.
Firm and toxic, their blood-sucking ability is unique.
Unlike traditional Golems, Zolrem move by a mysterious aura, not magic.
Although a Kepa by name, it actually comes from the demon realm.
An evil goblin summoned by the Vubbes. It sometimes appear even in areas where Vubbes are not found.
A mutant monster that looks like a dolphin. Its other features correspond to a small Stone Whale.
Although a clyra type because of its sharp tail, this monster seems to have transformed from a pumpkin.
As demons become more populous, new varieties of them appear. Infroholder is one of these new types of demon.
In the past this animal was quite friendly towards humans, but now it's even more dangerous than a bear.
The Amorites are durahans whose armor is stained by evil forces.
Is that another tail hanging on its back?
A demon that respects the strong and is cruel to the weak. Nonetheless, its aggression trivializes this characteristic.
It is uncertain which monster Infrobirk resembles, but it certainly is ferocious.
They kill their fellow demons out of boredom.
A small monster that is part turtle and part mineral. It prefers living in solitude rather than in a group.
Because of its appearance, novice miners often try to mine the crystal on the spider's back and are attacked.
Those who see Filibo as a small and cute critter will quickly be injured by it.
Acting as Mirtis' scout minion, these bats once lived throughout the world but have grown into a large threat despite of their small bodies.
Although the Hogmas are smarter than the Vubbes and can use tools, their brutish instincts stifle any progress and lead to many stupid mistakes.
Levelheaded Hogmas are often seen taking the role of archers.
Some Hogmas have picked up abilities through experience but they still have Hogma instincts.
It is said that they receive their powers from human souls because they gather toward the injured.
This type of Ellom is toxic.
Merlog variant. Slight differences in the mutation process differentiates the variety of Merlogs.
This reptile monster attacks instinctively but shows as much abilities as its intelligence.
A Hogma whose intelligence and instinct give them leadership in the fight against humans.
A monster which is said to be created by demons using the Chupacabra.
It is both filthy in nature and surly in its appearance.
It is fierce against other monsters and humans, more so especially with insect type monsters.
Amphibians that have branched out and evolved to be able to hunt in arid areas, travelers should be wary of them.
A monster with a habit of baiting and attacking humans.
You can tell the origin of this beast just by its name or appearance.
Tama is a monster originating from the spores of some plants. It is unclear whether it will still grow from its current form.
Kepari are not related with the Kepa, and are instead akin to animals.
Since the disappearance of the Goddesses, one of the most bizarre change is that these water-dwelling creatures are now active on land.
It still tends to gravitate toward rotten flesh.
It is not yet clear what deforms into this monster.
Similar to the Lemur, but cold-resistant.
While they look like guardsmen, these Hogmas have extensive battle experience.
Compared to an average Hogmas, they are very stronger, but their intelligence is lower.
It is a monster that is formed by binding an animal with a mineral. In recent years, various forms of these monsters have been discovered.
It is one of several variations of Zinute.
A variety of Chupacabra dwell in various places, causing harm to both human life and crops.
Although small, it has grown bigger than its original state and hunts for meat throughout its life
While it has no eyes, Arma has a highly developed sense of hearing and smell.
It attacks people with a flame ball that it cherishes and carries around.
A monster variant that comes from a wizard's belongings. It is resistive to its original use.
A sad monster that can't fly.
While it was once a creature created by a wizard using the best magic available, it has now turned hostile to humans due to the influence of the demons.
When the demons captured the Mage Tower, this doll was greatly affected. In particular, it instinctively hates magic users.
The slime is an organism in the demon realm. Its population exploded after the time when the plant Geant, especially around the Mage Tower.
One of the demon's lower level creature.They possess a little bit of intelligence.
When botanists first discovered the Raflower, they planned on naming it Tripede, a name that has since been given to another monster.
A monster whose habitat has been relocated close to the volcano.
A hybrid monster that exhibit the advantages of having the body of two known beasts.
Ultanun have always been a flightless bird even before its deformation.
Don't let its cute appearance fool you. This monster will try to tear you apart, given the chance.
A Panto variant with distinctively high intelligence. They often show up with the other Panto variants.
The Panto Shaman is powerful, but it does not know were they are in a developing type of wizard. The obvious point is that you must pay more attention to them during combat.
A somewhat cute mutant that is always expressionless. They assemble together when chanting.
Moyabu has evolved from the Moya. It is more violent than the Moya.
When it comes to flight, Bavon would be better just floating there as is.
A carnivorous plant that uses bait to catch food. It shred its food into pieces before swallowing.
A three headed monster. It is hard to tell whether the main body is just one head or all three.
This beast that once exclusively roamed in the Demon realm. Nowadays it is found all over the world, endangering other wildlife and humans.
The demons have tamed Denden and uses it for their means.
If a moving poisonous mushroom makes you anxious, consider Doyor as an example.
The yellow grass on its body looks supple. But if you touch it, it can be quite painful .
The Rondo is not an animal found in our world, rather it is an animal that crossed from the demon realm.
The Terra Nymph are quite mischievous. One should be aware of their belongings, as they might steal them.
Although it appears to have no sharp edges, it will when in battle.
There are not too many cases of a fruit deformed monsters. Leafnut belongs to these few cases.
Its elongated pupils are a distinctive feature.
A Panto with excellent fighting skills and is one of the strongest subspecies in the forest.
The flowers around its neck are actually real flowers rather than decorations.
If you carelessly touch the leaves on its head, Mally will unleash its relentless anger towards you.
Be aware of the smoke that this creature spurts as it is highly toxic and will last for a while.
A bite from its sharp beak causes persistent pain, which may last for a while.
The edges of its wings are covered in poison. Touching it may cause paralysis.
A low-ranking demon who is always looking for opportunities to promote itself.
The Seedmia are very troublesome as they are able to shoot seeds over exceptionally long distances.
A moving tree monster that appeared after the Great Plant Cataclysm, it was named after its discoverer.
Galok is a monster who command workers in the demon realm.
Upent rapidly appeared from what once were flora with magical powers.
When the demons found glizardons, they immediately subjugated them into minions. Glizardons that aren't minions are still dangerous to humans.
The Corylus is a mutant hybrid between plants, animals and minerals.
The reduction in size isn't the only thing that got better after this beast mutated.
It is simple and effective for Beeteros to camouflage. Please do not touch the swaying leaf as it can stab you.
A mutated mantis. It has gotten stronger and has developed the ability to camouflage.
Egnomes carry a stern look. The more stern it looks, the more powerful it is.
After mutating, Beetow has developed an unreasonable and venomous nature. Its aggression has also become more significant.
I'll have a big sickle with their bodies to pound sister.
Carcashu is a fungus. Its toxins are strong, but there are parts of it that can be eaten.
The Black Maize looks deceptively delicious, eating one will certainly cause addiction.
This monster was bred by the demons and is known for its poisonous abilities.
Please don't assume that Lapasape can only be encountered in the deep forest, as it sometimes prowl outside to eat human crops.
Its appearance did not change much, but its physicality has. Lives near water.
This monster was once the size of a little finger, but it has since grown greatly.
This monster has evolved from a bird and has since lost its ability to fly.
The Dumaro is a newly discovered monster, which developed its toxic abilities after the Great Plant Cataclysm.
The Lichenclops doesn't only have good eye sight, their sense of smell is also exceptional.
Infroblood is a case where plant spores transform into monsters. It can float.
Ticen wanders around with a spear, it tends to group with other Ticen variants.
A tip of Tucen's tail is made out of minerals.
Since it retains its memory before deformation, this monster has grudges against the people who felled it.
Although this monster looks small, it has already reached its adulthood. So it might only grow just a bit more.
The Woodfung is closely related to witchcraft.
They exhibit a unique hull that is a mix between stone and iron.
It is speculated whether this underground spirit has been deformed and corrupted.
It has been said that the Helgacercle was made by the servants of the demon realm's aristocrats.

Consumed HP/SP/Stamina can be recovered through the following options.
Spontaneous Recovery is slow compared to other recovery methods, but it does not require the player to do anything.
[Potion Recovery]: Recover HP/SP/Stamina immediately using potions.
Potions have a cooldown timer before they can be re-used.
[Tree Root Crystal]: Destroy Tree Root Crystals to recover Stamina.
Tree Root Crystals are randomly generated around the field.
[Rest Mode]: Using the bonfire during Rest Mode speeds up your recovery.
Recovery during Rest Mode is faster than Spontaneous Recovery, and it is even faster if you use a bonfire during Rest Mode.
Overkill will be activated if you kill the monster with a strong finish.
Overkill will be activated if you do more damage with a powerful attack to a monster than its remaining HP.
Destroying a Tree Root Crystal recovers your Stamina.
There are many Tree Root Crystals in every field.
The Stamina of all the players around you will be replenished if you destroy the Tree Root Crystals.
Some particular skills may overheat when used over a certain number of times.
If Overheat is triggered, that skill goes on cool-down and you will be unable to use it for a while.
Overheat will trigger when the gauge on the skill icon at the bottom is fully charged.
To prevent skills from overheating, you can alternate between using power attacks and basic attacks.
Overheat can be suppressed to use many skills.
Once overheated, you won't be able to use the affected skill for a while.
The used number of relevant skill will be initialize after a while.

Swordsmen are warriors who have strong physical abilities. They use various weapons to deal with enemies up close at the front line.
Highlanders are tough fighters and use two-hand swords. They make enemies collide with each other or terrain so they are great for handling multiple enemies.
Peltastas are defensive warriors who use shields to block enemy attacks and provoke the enemy.
Hoplites use spears with a long attack range. They gain a bonus when fighting against strong, large-sized enemies.
Centurions command the battle with formations.
Barbarians are reckless and aggressive warriors who are not bound to any formats in battle and would do anything to claim victory in their hands.
Cataphracts use two hand spears. They are the cavalry who break through and scatter the enemy formations.
Rodeleros ambush and disintegrate enemies. Their defensive skills using shields are effective for blocking long range attacks.
Wizards use magic to block attacks and protect themselves. They can cast powerful and concentrated spells, dealing damage to a single target or multiple enemies in an area.
Pyromancers use continuous fire magic to fight against multiple enemies.
Cryomancers use ice magic to freeze foes or protect their allies from enemies by using ice walls.
Psychokinos use psychokinesis to control gravity or pull enemies and throw them around.
Sorcerers summon devils and control them.
Linkers link allies together to reduce the damage received or connect enemies to amplify the damage inflicted.
This class accumulates the dead parts of monsters.
Thaumaturges use magic that changes the attributes and size of targets. They can shrink enemies or strengthen allies to aid them in battle.
Elementalists use the power of elements and can cast powerful magic attacks. However, their spells have a long cooldown time, so it is recommended to cooperate with other players.
Archers use bows and various secondary equipment. Their specialties are long range and moving attacks.
Hunters are trainers who hunt enemies using companions. Companions use skills which require cooperation with their owners, such as biting and holding onto enemies or finding hidden targets.
Quarrel Shooters use a crossbow and shield for strategic combat. They can defend against long-range attacks and use catapult skills against approaching enemies.
Rangers specialize in fighting against multiple enemies with their quick and long-range attacks.
Sappers are archers who install traps and lure enemies into them.
Wugushis specialize in using various poisons to attack or bewitch enemies.
Scouts specialize in reconnaissance and infiltration. They use stealth to hide themselves and convey the enemy's situation to allies for an advantage in battle.
Clerics heal and protect allies through the blessings of the Goddess, while knocking down their enemies with powerful blows.
Priests are clerics who give blessings and resurrect the dead with their holy powers.
Krivis are priests who use divine fire to help allies recover or to deal massive damage to the enemy.
Bokors use voodoo skills to raise the dead or curse their enemies to attack them from afar.
Sadhu can use their soul to assault enemies with unseen attacks or convey their powers to other players.
Dievdirbys carve and place holy statues which protect allies or attack enemies.
Monks are clerics who train in martial arts through the blessing of the Goddess.
Pardoners are clerics who don't deny increasing their wealth through the Goddess's blessing.
Paladins use their holy power to protect allies and vanquish enemies through the blessings of the Goddess.

The Strength stat increases your physical damage and critical damage.

Highlanders are tough fighters who use Two-Hand swords. They make enemies collide with each other or the terrain, so they are great for handling multiple enemies.
Centurions command the battle with formations. They control other soldiers to use different formations depending on the situation.
Corsairs are specialized in dual-wielding and ambushing enemies from behind. Anyone who joins the Corsairs' party becomes a pirate.
Doppelsoeldners are mercenaries who endure high risk for high rewards. They dangerously expose themselves to the enemies and receive high attack power or high EXP.
Squires are warriors who support fellow soldiers. They support by repairing and enhancing others' weapons or install a basecamp to aid the team.
Alchemists use alchemy to enhance gems and synthesize or craft items.
Sorcerers summon demons which they control to fight enemies or even use as mounts.
Chronomancers are wizards who control time. They stop, speed up, or change back time to help fellow soldiers.
Necromancers are wizards who use dead body parts. They attack or make summons using the dead body parts collected.
Rogues are combat professionals that will do anything for victory. They're specialized to ambush enemies from behind using bows and daggers.
Schwarzer Reiters maneuver quickly. They specialize in diverse shooting techniques using a pistol.
Fletchers make and use special arrows. Various arrows result in powerful attacks depending on the type of enemy and combat situation.
The Falconer controls a Hawk. Hawks may be fussy, but they become reliable companions when trained well.
Druids are clerics that use the power of nature. They control plants to help allies or transform into monsters and use monsters' abilities.
Oracles are priests that use foresight. They can predict or interfere with enemy's attacks and determine their fate.

FAQ : Lodge{nl}1)You can change the name of your lodge by clicking "Lodge Settings". {nl}2)You can buy Lodge skins using iCoins by clicking "Change Lodge".{nl}3)You select your desired channel from the Lodge.

FAQ : Character HP, SP, STA {nl} 1) You can check your character's information on the upper left side of the screen. {nl}2) STA: This is stamina. When your STA is 0, you can only walk and can't run. {nl} It is also used when learning certain attributes. {nl} You can recover STA by destroying Tree Root Crystals or by using Stamina Pills. {nl} Stamina Pills can be bought through shop or can be earned by completing quests or defeating boss monsters.

FAQ : Character Level and Class Level {nl}You can check the info at the lower part of the screen. {nl}2) Character Level: this is your character's level. {nl}3) Class Level: this is the level of the class you chose. {nl} You can advance to another class when you reach level 15.

FAQ : Quick Slot{nl}1) You can add items or skills to the quick slot at the lower part of your screen. {nl}2) Skills are automatically added to quick slot when you learn skills. {nl}3)You can use up to 40 quick slots. {nl}4) Quick slots can be locked or unlocked. {nl}You cannot add or remove items or skill in quick slot when it is locked.
FAQ : Changing Channels{nl}1) You can change channels by clicking on the channel button above the minimap. {nl}2) You can change channels in the Lodge before entering the world.

FAQ : Rest Mode{nl}1) Use "insert" key to switch to Rest Mode. {nl}2) HP, SP, STA is recovered. {nl}3) You can set up a camp fire, manufacture items, enhance gems, combine cards, etc in Rest Mode{nl} You need "firewood" to build a bonfire. {nl} HP, SP, STA is recovered faster when you use a bonfire.{nl}Other functions will be added in the future.

FAQ : Durability and Potential{nl}1) Durability : It will start to decrease a bit when you play with the equipment on.{nl}    When the durability decreases under the certain level, the item's icon will be displayed on the right side of quick slot.{nl}   When the durability completely diminishes, you won't be benefited from the equipment's effects.{nl}2) Potential : It will decrease when you are trading an equipment item or enhance an item, and the item with it's potential all depleted will can't be traded nor enhanced.

FAQ : Enhancement{nl}1) Weapons and armors can be enhanced using the anvil. {nl}2) You can buy anvils from the Tools Merchants in town. {nl}3) Silver is required everytime you enhance an item.{nl}4)The enhancement of weapons and armor has a 100% success rate till +5 and +3 respectively. The chance of failure after the next enhancement will increase.{nl} If an enhancement fails, your enhancement level will reset and the Potential of your item decreases.

FAQ : Attributes{nl}1) There are attributes that you can learn from the Masters of your class. {nl}2) You can learn different types of attributes depending on the class. {nl} For example, if you advance to Highlander, you can learn Two-Hand sword attributes from Highlander Master and use Two-Hand swords. {nl}3) Masters who teach attributes are located all around the map.
FAQ : Charge Skill{nl}1) Charge skills are triggered only when you press down the quick slot button of the skill. {nl}2) Skill is canceled when you are attacked while using the skill.
FAQ : System Menu{nl}1) You can change to "Joypad UI Mode" from game settings when using Joypad. {nl}2) You can play using "Low-spec Mode" if your computer has low system requirements.

FAQ : Chatting{nl}1) Shout: Enter "/y" before your message to show your message to all players. {nl} But, you need the "Megaphone" to do so. {nl}2) Party Chat: Enter "/p" before your message to chat with your party. {nl}Whisper: Enter "/w Team Name" before your message to talk privately with the player of that Team Name.

FAQ : Inventory Weight{nl}1) Show the weight of the items you can carry. {nl}2) Weight increases by 5 when you increase your CON stat after you level up. {nl}3) When the items you carry are overweight, your character will walk regardless of the STA.

FAQ : Minimap, Zone Map, World Map{nl}1) Click "+","-" buttons on the minimap to zoom-in or zoom-out. {nl}2) Click on "M" on the minimap or press "M" on your keyboard to view the full map of the zone (zone map) you are in. {nl}3) Use "N" on your keyboard to view the world map.

Press {img Alt 40 40} to immediately stop your character movement.
Press {img space 40 40} to face your target.
Use the Map to check your current location and other important areas.
Use {img M 40 40} to check the map of your current area.

{nl} {nl}The minimap icon displays the information of NPC locations of current map. {nl}{img minimap_leader 25 25} is your current location. {nl}{img minimap_1_MAIN 25 25} is the target area of a quest in progress. {nl}{img minimap_0 25 25} is the location of important NPCs in the area. {nl}{img minimap_goddess 25 25} is the Goddess statue for warp. {nl}{img minimap_board 25 25} is the bulletin board containing various information. {nl}{img minimap_portal 25 25} is the path to move to other areas.{nl} {nl}
Press {img N 40 40} to open World Map.
Only the areas you have already been to will be activated.{nl}Areas you haven't been to will not be shown in the World Map.
Hover your mouse over the activated area {nl}to see the map of explored areas.
Use Status Points obtained through leveling up to upgrade your character's abilities.
Press {img F1 40 40} to open Character Information window and view the character's status.

Use STR/CON/INT/SPR/DEX to make your character stronger. {nl} {nl} STR : Increase Physical Attack and Critical Attack {nl} {nl} CON : Increase max HP, HP Recovery, Block, Critical Resistance and max Inventory Weight {nl} {nl} INT : Increase Magic Attack and Block Penetration {nl}{nl} SPR : Increase max SP and SP Recovery {nl} {nl} DEX : Increase Accuracy, Evasion and Critical Chance {nl}
You can preview the effects from the screen below.
You can manage the skills of your character through the skill window.
Press {img F3 40 40} to open Skill window.
Press {img skillup 40 40} button to increase Skill level.
Make your character even stronger by learning Attributes from the Master NPC's of each class.
You can learn Attributes from the Master NPC's.
You need silver to learn attributes. {nl}Also, some attribute require time to master.
You can use the Attributes after you learn it, {nl}and you cannot learn another Attribute while one is in training.
Some Attributes may be disabled as needed.
You can Advance your class when you reach Class Lv 15.
After selecting a Class to Advance to, you will receive an Advancement Quest from the Class Master.
Once you begin the Advancement Quest, you cannot change your class until the next Advancement.
You can check your items, equipments, money, and weight through the Inventory.
Press {img F2 40 40} to open Inventroy window.
Upper part of the Inventory window shows items that the character equipped.
Items in Inventory are arranged by item types. {nl}Press Arrange to arrange inventory by name.
{nl}{nl}Use the search function to find items in inventory.
{nl}{nl}The lower part shows total carry weight of your items, funds, and iCoins.
Quests available are found in the Quest window.
Press {img F5 40 40} to view availble quests or quests in progress.
{nl}{nl}You can restart abandoned quests by pressing
button. Some quests cannot be abandoned.
{nl}{nl}Track quests by marking the checkbox in front of the quest title.
Check your character's game progress or rankings in Adventure Journal.
Your character's progress is recorded in the Adventure Journal. Press {img F4 40 40} to view.
You can earn Adventure Index through Items, Monsters, Crafting, Map, and Game Progression.
Press {img F1 40 40} to open Character Information window and choose the Achievement tab to view character's achievements.
Revive dead characters by using Resurrection.
A character will die when its HP reaches 0 and become
. {nl}{nl}Durability of equipped items will decrease drastically when character becomes incapable of combat.
{nl}{nl}Gems in your inventory will be dropped when you die inside a dungeon.
You can create a party to play with other players.
Press {img F6 40 40} to open the Party window.{nl}{nl}Press 'Create' button below to create party.
You can set your play style and preferred oarty formation in Members tab.{nl}{nl}This information will be used when you use Search Party function..
When you find players matching your conditions, {nl}{img mouseclick_right 40 40} to invite player to Party.
You can enjoy Party Events with other party members.
You can join each content and feature when certain conditions are met.
You can set the Party Name, Description, Item and EXP distribution rules, etc in Settings.
You can check the list of Public Parties on the right.
View information of monsters nearby or when you face the monster.
Each monster has an element and defense property.
While in Rest Mode, light bonfire to speed up recovery.
{nl}{nl}[Bonfire] Light a Bonfire during Rest Mode to speed up recovery.
Restoring Naturally is very slow compared to other methods, but does not require any control or conditions.
{nl}{nl}[Restore by Potion] : Restore HP/SP/STA immediately using various potions.
Potions have a cooldown timer before they can be re-used.
{nl}{nl}[Destroy Tree Root Crystal] : Destroy the Tree Root Crystal to restore the Stamina of all nearby characters.
Destroying a Tree Root Crystal recovers your Stamina.
Stamina of all the players nearby will be restored when you destroy Tree Root Crystal.
Team Battle League is a 5:5 team battle among players.
If Party and all party members press accept, system will search for opponents. When matching opponent party is found, you will move to battle zone to begin the battle.
You need to win two of three matches to win.
You can obtain item recipes from monster loot, shops, and quests.
{nl}{nl}To craft, press {img Insert 40 40} and change to Rest Mode.
{nl}{nl}If you have all required materials, press
You can add names or memos on your crafted items.

button to trade. {nl}To trade multiple items, use {img shift 40 40}+{img mouseclick_right 40 40} to set quantity. {nl}{nl}[Sell] : {img mouseclick_right 40 40} on the items you want to sell from your inventory, and set quantity, then press
button to trade. {nl}Double {img mouseclick_right 40 40} to sell all of that item. {nl}{nl}
Items sold to the shops can be bought back.
{img mouseclick_right 40 40} on the item from 'Items Sold' below {nl}to buy back item or delete it from the list.
Enhance your equipment to increase its abilities.
You need money and Anvil to enhance.
can be purchased from Tools Merchant or obtained from monsters.
{nl}{nl}{img mouseclick_right 40 40} on the Anvil, then select item to open Enhancement window.
{nl}{nl}When your equipment is enhanced, its abililties increase.
{nl}{nl}Weapon above +4 will lose a potential and its abilities will be reset when enhancement fails. Item will be destroyed when Potential drops to 0.
Repain items with low durability through the Blacksmith NPC.
Repain items with low durability in Item Repair window.
{nl}{nl}Select an item then click Repair to restore durability to 100%.
Effects differ based on the type of Gem and Equipment.
{nl}{nl}Increas Gem level through Gem Enhnacement in Rest Mode.
Gem enhancement requires other Gems or Gem Abrasives.
{nl}{nl}Insert Gems in the item sockets to add additional effects.
Some items may not have sockets. For such items, you can add sockets through the Blacksmith NPC. {nl}{nl}Adding sockets will require a fee and reduce the item's Potential by 1.
{nl}{nl} {img mouseclick_right 40 40} on the Gem to see which items are compatible.
Click on the item to insert the Gem.{nl}Hover the cursor over an item to view its Gems.
The Gem's level will may decrease by 1 when removed.
Sub-Weapons refer to all right-hand weapons except Shields.
Your character will attack with the Sub-Weapon.
If the Sub-Weapon has special properties, weapon effects will apply.
[Trade] {img mouseclick_right 40 40} on the player you want to trade with and select Trade.
Select an item to trade by {img mouseclick_right 40 40} on the item in your inventory.
{nl}{nl}[Market] The Market allows you to trade items with many other players.
You can use the Market through the Market Manager.
You can look at items offered by other players, and purchase items from the list.
You can also register your items to sell.
{img mouseclick_right 40 40} on the item you want to sell from your inventory, then set qty and selling price.
{nl}{nl}[Buy-in Shop] Press {img F1 40 40} to open Information window and press Character to open Buy-in shop.
Register the items you need, then set qty and price for other players to sell items to you.
Buy-in Shop will remain even if you disconnect from server.
Use warp to quickly move to your desired area.
is used to warp between Goddess Statues when activated.
{nl}{nl}You can use the active Goddess Statue to teleport to other areas with an active Goddess Statue.
You can also use the Warp Scroll to warp immediately.
However, when using the Warp Scroll, you can only warp to areas with activated statues.
By using the Warp Scroll again, you will be warped to your last location.{nl}Returning location will be shown as
and does not consume the Warp Scroll when you warp back.
Warp Scrolls can be bought from shops or obtained from quests.
You can use the 'Return' button to complete quests easily.

You can add the item to the collection by dragging the item from inventory to the Collection.
{nl}{nl}Items added can be moved back to your inventory by {img mouseclick_right 40 40}.
Removing items from a completed Collection will mark it as incomplete and remove its effect.{nl}Only completed Collections give collection effects.
Press {img SPACE 40 40} in front of the Supplies Box to retrieve it.
Adopt and train Companions. They aid you in combat and transport.
You can adopt a Companion by paying the fee required.
{nl}{nl}Companion follows and helps the character in combat and receives EXP.
can ride the Companion in combat.
Press {img F9 40 40} to view information of the companion following you.
Companions consume Stamina when you bring them along. Companion's movement speed will decrease when there is no Stamina. {nl}{nl}Press the Switch button to change the Companion's status to rest mode.
You can recover Companion's Stamina by feeding the Companion. {nl}{nl}HP will be recovered fully and Stamina will be recovered partially.
Companion food can be purchased from Companion Trader NPC.
Train your Companion through the Companion Trader to increase its abilities. A Training fee is required.
Monsters found in dungeons will attack characters on sight.
Gems may be lost when you die in dungeons so be careful!
When you die in dungeons, press
to revive at the entrance outside the dungeon.
Receive beneficial effects when you worship the Goddess Statues.
enables you to warp to other areas.
There are many types of treasure chests {nl}and you can obtain special items from them.
You can receive the rewards by pressing {img SPACE 40 40} from level 1 treasure chests.
You can obtain the key through{nl}quest progress.
Use the Social Function to interact with other players.
[Friends] You can check your friends using {img F7 40 40}. Users should agree each other in order to add each other into their Friend List.
Use {img mouseclick_right 40 40} to send a proposal to a character that you want to become your friend.
You can check your friends' log in status and their locations.
You can check it from Character Info.
Add Magic Amulet on weapons and shields for additional effects.
After {img mouseclick_left 40 40} Magic Amulet, when you {img mouseclick_right 40 40} the equipment, a magic amulet will be attached to the equipment.
When attached, a magic amulet will consume Potential.
You can check the attached amulet from the tooltip of the item.
You can't eliminate the attached magic amulet unlike a gem and can't enhance it.
When you are equipped with the equipment with a magic amulet attached, you can see the magic amulet swaying from the equipment.
Overkill will be activated if you inflict more damages with a powerful attack to a monster than its remaining HP.
You can engage in 1:1 Card Battle with an other player using monsters cards.
When you defeat a Boss monster, you will obtain a monster card.
When you input, Card Battle Table will be opened.{nl}You opponent can participate Card Battle by {img SPACE 40 40} key.
When you register a card at Inventory that you will use for Card Battle and press Decide, you will be ready. The registered card will be shown as undisclosed to your opponent.
When both sides decide on the cards, they disclose their cards and the win/loss will be decided using Roulette.
Win/Loss will be decided by comparing the monsters' number of legs, height, weight, number of stars and etc.
Based on the information on the cards, win/loss will be decided.
The winner will obtain the loser's card
You can use the obtained card as a material to enhance the other card you have which will increase the number of stars
By pressing {img Insert 40 40}, you can go into Rest mode to use it.
When Party Leader accepts the boss hunting mission, go to the area with your party members to start the boss hunting.

When Party Leader accepts the mission, you can go to Fedimian Mercenary Reception Office to start the mission with your party members. When the party members are all gathered, Party Leader should talk to the receptionist, Ramda to move to the mission location to start the mission.
When Party Leader accepts the party quest, party members can also receive the quest. After receiving the party quest, move to to the quest location to start the quest.
When Party Leader accepts Team Battle League, you can compete against other parties by forming a team with your party members. After accepting, please wait until your opponent is selected.
